{"title":"Go Nuts: RideFast Racing Nut Jobs Tubeless Valves are Optimized for Flat Repairs","link":"https://bikerumor.com/2021/07/09/ridefast-nut-jobs-tubeless-valves/","date":1625867814000,"content":"<div id=\"readability-page-1\" class=\"page\"><div><p>It sucks to get stuck roadside or trailside, with a flat tire and a stuck valve you can’t unstick. Happily, Nut Jobs are here to help. (What?)</p><p>That’s correct; Southern California-based wheel builder RideFast Racing designs its new Nut Jobs alloy tubeless valves to help ease the pain of valves fused with <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/2020/08/28/aasq-82-stans-no-tubes-peatys-joes-no-flats-and-muc-off-seal-up-your-worries-on-tubeless-sealant/\">tire sealant</a> or trail debris. The brand collaborates with local multi-tool company Fix MFG to deliver its new valves, which feature 2 hardware options to aid in valve removal: a 10mm hex nut (stem) and a 4mm Allen key (base).</p><h3>A Nut Job’s Life: Inspiration and Specs</h3><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/09181149/Wrench-Only-2.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/09181149/Wrench-Only-2.jpg?ezimgfmt=rs:484x645/rscb25/ng:webp/ngcb25\" alt=\"\" width=\"1200\" height=\"1600\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/09181149/Wrench-Only-2.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb25 1200w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/09181149/Wrench-Only-2-225x300.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb25 225w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/09181149/Wrench-Only-2-800x1067.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb25 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/09181149/Wrench-Only-2-90x120.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb25 90w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/09181149/Wrench-Only-2-768x1024.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb25 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/09181149/Wrench-Only-2-1152x1536.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb25 1152w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/09181149/Wrench-Only-2-696x928.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb25 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/09181149/Wrench-Only-2-1068x1424.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb25 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/09181149/Wrench-Only-2-315x420.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb25 315w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb25 src ng ngcb25 srcset\" data-ezsrc=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/09181149/Wrench-Only-2.jpg?ezimgfmt=rs:484x645/rscb25/ng:webp/ngcb25\" ezoid=\"0.4759755135223418\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/09181149/Wrench-Only-2.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb25 1200w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/09181149/Wrench-Only-2-225x300.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb25 225w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/09181149/Wrench-Only-2-800x1067.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb25 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/09181149/Wrench-Only-2-90x120.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb25 90w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/09181149/Wrench-Only-2-768x1024.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb25 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/09181149/Wrench-Only-2-1152x1536.jpg?ezimgfmt